<subSubSection pageId="44" pageNumber="45" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1437,1267,1546]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1267,1293]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Adult males of 
<taxonomicName authority="De &amp; Bueno-Villegas &amp; Rafael, 2021" authorityName="De &amp; Bueno-Villegas &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="2021" box="[457,545,1267,1294]" class="Diplopoda" family="Aphelidesmidae" genus="Haematotropis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="driki" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[457,477,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[492,545,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">driki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[553,644,1267,1293]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[553,644,1267,1293]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differ from other 
<taxonomicName box="[849,1105,1267,1293]" class="Diplopoda" family="Aphelidesmidae" genus="Haematotropis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[849,1016,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Haematotropis</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
based on the following combination of characters: gonopod with LP1 long and tapered, hemispheric apex, projected the lateral of acropodite (
<figureCitation box="[160,298,1339,1365]" captionStart="FIGURE 33" captionStartId="46.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[214,1373,181,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-22@46.[214,1373,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURE 33. Right gonopod of Haematotropis driki sp. nov., holotype ♂ (MNRJ). A. Mesal view. B. Dorsal view. C. Lateral view. D. Ventral view. Yellow scale indicates when VP1 exceeds the width of ventral region of acropodite. Abbreviations: Ac = acropodite; Ca = cannula; Cx = coxa; LP1 = Lateral Process 1; Pf = Prefemur; S = Solenomere; Sg = spermatic groove; Ste = setae; VP1 = Ventral Process 1. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5653803" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5653803/files/figure.png" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Fig. 33A–D</figureCitation>
); opening of solenomere located at distal end of acropodite; solenomere without projection (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 33" captionStartId="46.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[214,1373,181,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-22@46.[214,1373,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURE 33. Right gonopod of Haematotropis driki sp. nov., holotype ♂ (MNRJ). A. Mesal view. B. Dorsal view. C. Lateral view. D. Ventral view. Yellow scale indicates when VP1 exceeds the width of ventral region of acropodite. Abbreviations: Ac = acropodite; Ca = cannula; Cx = coxa; LP1 = Lateral Process 1; Pf = Prefemur; S = Solenomere; Sg = spermatic groove; Ste = setae; VP1 = Ventral Process 1. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5653803" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5653803/files/figure.png" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Fig. 33A, C, D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
