</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1436,1699,2014]" box="[151,1070,1699,1726]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,318,1699,1725]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Size and form</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus box="[332,432,1699,1725]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">holotype</typeStatus>
<specimenCount box="[439,462,1700,1726]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
). Body length = 66 and wide = 
<quantity box="[817,885,1699,1726]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" unit="mm" value="8.0">8 mm</quantity>
. TL/GW = 8.25.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1436,1699,2014]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,1735,1761]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Coloration</emphasis>
(long preserved in 70% ethanol). Head, prozonite, metazonite and telson light brown, antennomeres, sides of metazonite, paranota and legs yellow (
<figureCitation box="[757,896,1771,1797]" captionStart="FIGURE 32" captionStartId="45.[151,250,1939,1963]" captionTargetBox="[201,1386,741,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-250@45.[201,1386,741,1915]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="FIGURE 32. Somatic features of Haematotropis driki sp. nov., holotype ♂ (MNRJ). A. Head and body rings 1–4, dorsal view. B. Head and body rings 1–6, lateral view. C. Body rings 8–12, dorsal view. D. Body rings 18–20, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5653801" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5653801/files/figure.png" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Fig. 32A–D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1436,1699,2014]" box="[199,960,1807,1833]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,270,1807,1833]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Head.</emphasis>
Dorsal surface smooth and shiny, without microgranulations.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1436,1699,2014]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,282,1843,1869]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Trunk.</emphasis>
Collum 
<quantity box="[378,442,1843,1870]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[511,575,1844,1870]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" unit="mm" value="7.0">7 mm</quantity>
wide; dorsal surface of all rings smooth and shiny, without microgranulation; posterolateral margins slightly concave (
<figureCitation box="[616,757,1879,1906]" captionStart="FIGURE 32" captionStartId="45.[151,250,1939,1963]" captionTargetBox="[201,1386,741,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-250@45.[201,1386,741,1915]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="FIGURE 32. Somatic features of Haematotropis driki sp. nov., holotype ♂ (MNRJ). A. Head and body rings 1–4, dorsal view. B. Head and body rings 1–6, lateral view. C. Body rings 8–12, dorsal view. D. Body rings 18–20, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5653801" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5653801/files/figure.png" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Fig. 32A, B</figureCitation>
). Rings 2–19: prozonite and metazonite smooth and shiny, without microgranulation in dorsal region of all rings. Anterolateral teeth on paranota of rings 2–4 (
<figureCitation box="[1249,1339,1915,1941]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1714,1738]" captionTargetBox="[281,1307,181,1690]" captionTargetId="figure-22@8.[281,1307,181,1690]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 2. General somatic features of Haematotropis Jeekel, 2000. A. H. jurutiensis sp. nov., non-type ♂ (MPEG), body ring 7, ventral view. B. H. jurutiensis sp. nov., non-type ♂ (MPEG), body ring 9 (highlighting the microgranulations), ventral view. C. H. jurutiensis sp. nov., non-type ♂ (MPEG), body ring 7, red arrow indicates the wrinkles close to paranota, ventral view. D. H. jurutiensis sp. nov., non-type ♂ (MPEG), body ring 8, red arrow indicates rounded projections on ventral surfaces, ventral view. E. H. jurutiensis sp. nov., non-type ♂ (MPEG), metazonite of body ring 8, red arrow indicates the microgranulations on anterior and posterior margins, dorsal view. F. H. megalcensis sp. nov. non-type ♂ (IBSP), body ring 10, red arrow indicates the microgranulations on anterior and posterior margins, ventral view. G. H. callipa, holotype ♂ (MfN), head and body rings 1–4, red arrow indicates a depression on collum or anterolateral teeth, dorsalateral view. Scale bars: 300 μm (A, E), 200 μm (C, D, F), 100 μm (B), 1 mm (G)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5653710" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5653710/files/figure.png" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Fig. 2G</figureCitation>
). Lateral margins of ring 2 not projected posteriad (
<figureCitation box="[623,758,1951,1978]" captionStart="FIGURE 32" captionStartId="45.[151,250,1939,1963]" captionTargetBox="[201,1386,741,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-250@45.[201,1386,741,1915]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="FIGURE 32. Somatic features of Haematotropis driki sp. nov., holotype ♂ (MNRJ). A. Head and body rings 1–4, dorsal view. B. Head and body rings 1–6, lateral view. C. Body rings 8–12, dorsal view. D. Body rings 18–20, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5653801" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5653801/files/figure.png" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Fig. 32A, B</figureCitation>
). Gonopodal aperture elliptical, approximately 
<quantity box="[1289,1375,1951,1978]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" unit="mm" value="1.7">1.7 mm</quantity>
wide and 1.0 mm long at midpoints. Telson smooth and shiny, without microgranulations.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1437,151,717]" box="[199,788,151,177]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,262,151,177]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Legs.</emphasis>
Smooth and shiny, without microgranulations.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1437,151,717]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,186,212]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Gonopods.</emphasis>
Right gonopod structure as follows: coxa with lateral swelling at midlength (
<figureCitation box="[1194,1330,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 33" captionStartId="46.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[214,1373,181,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-22@46.[214,1373,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURE 33. Right gonopod of Haematotropis driki sp. nov., holotype ♂ (MNRJ). A. Mesal view. B. Dorsal view. C. Lateral view. D. Ventral view. Yellow scale indicates when VP1 exceeds the width of ventral region of acropodite. Abbreviations: Ac = acropodite; Ca = cannula; Cx = coxa; LP1 = Lateral Process 1; Pf = Prefemur; S = Solenomere; Sg = spermatic groove; Ste = setae; VP1 = Ventral Process 1. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5653803" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5653803/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Fig. 33A, C</figureCitation>
); acropodite elongated, about four times as long as prefemur; median region expanded, cup-shaped in ventral view, with a concavity and cavity (
<figureCitation box="[398,502,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 33" captionStartId="46.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[214,1373,181,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-22@46.[214,1373,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURE 33. Right gonopod of Haematotropis driki sp. nov., holotype ♂ (MNRJ). A. Mesal view. B. Dorsal view. C. Lateral view. D. Ventral view. Yellow scale indicates when VP1 exceeds the width of ventral region of acropodite. Abbreviations: Ac = acropodite; Ca = cannula; Cx = coxa; LP1 = Lateral Process 1; Pf = Prefemur; S = Solenomere; Sg = spermatic groove; Ste = setae; VP1 = Ventral Process 1. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5653803" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5653803/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Fig. 33D</figureCitation>
); distal region of acropodite lightly sinuous, not bifurcate, curved ventrally at a 60° angle (
<figureCitation box="[227,364,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 33" captionStartId="46.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[214,1373,181,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-22@46.[214,1373,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURE 33. Right gonopod of Haematotropis driki sp. nov., holotype ♂ (MNRJ). A. Mesal view. B. Dorsal view. C. Lateral view. D. Ventral view. Yellow scale indicates when VP1 exceeds the width of ventral region of acropodite. Abbreviations: Ac = acropodite; Ca = cannula; Cx = coxa; LP1 = Lateral Process 1; Pf = Prefemur; S = Solenomere; Sg = spermatic groove; Ste = setae; VP1 = Ventral Process 1. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5653803" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5653803/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Fig. 33A, C</figureCitation>
); VP1 emarginated on the posterior region, not very evident, not exceeding the width of ventral region of acropodite, in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[567,704,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 33" captionStartId="46.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[214,1373,181,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-22@46.[214,1373,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURE 33. Right gonopod of Haematotropis driki sp. nov., holotype ♂ (MNRJ). A. Mesal view. B. Dorsal view. C. Lateral view. D. Ventral view. Yellow scale indicates when VP1 exceeds the width of ventral region of acropodite. Abbreviations: Ac = acropodite; Ca = cannula; Cx = coxa; LP1 = Lateral Process 1; Pf = Prefemur; S = Solenomere; Sg = spermatic groove; Ste = setae; VP1 = Ventral Process 1. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5653803" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5653803/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Fig. 33A, C</figureCitation>
); VP2 absent; LP1 long and tapered, hemispheric apex, projected towards the lateral of acropodite (
<figureCitation box="[533,671,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 33" captionStartId="46.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[214,1373,181,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-22@46.[214,1373,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURE 33. Right gonopod of Haematotropis driki sp. nov., holotype ♂ (MNRJ). A. Mesal view. B. Dorsal view. C. Lateral view. D. Ventral view. Yellow scale indicates when VP1 exceeds the width of ventral region of acropodite. Abbreviations: Ac = acropodite; Ca = cannula; Cx = coxa; LP1 = Lateral Process 1; Pf = Prefemur; S = Solenomere; Sg = spermatic groove; Ste = setae; VP1 = Ventral Process 1. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5653803" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5653803/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Fig. 33C, D</figureCitation>
), LP2, LP3 and DP absent. Opening of solenomere located at distal end of acropodite, without projection. Solenomere without projection (
<figureCitation box="[943,1115,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 33" captionStartId="46.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[214,1373,181,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-22@46.[214,1373,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURE 33. Right gonopod of Haematotropis driki sp. nov., holotype ♂ (MNRJ). A. Mesal view. B. Dorsal view. C. Lateral view. D. Ventral view. Yellow scale indicates when VP1 exceeds the width of ventral region of acropodite. Abbreviations: Ac = acropodite; Ca = cannula; Cx = coxa; LP1 = Lateral Process 1; Pf = Prefemur; S = Solenomere; Sg = spermatic groove; Ste = setae; VP1 = Ventral Process 1. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5653803" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5653803/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Fig. 33A, C, D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="45" pageNumber="46" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1437,151,717]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,439,465]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Remarks.</emphasis>
All species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jeekel" authorityYear="2000" box="[479,646,439,464]" class="Diplopoda" family="Aphelidesmidae" genus="Haematotropis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[479,646,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Haematotropis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have peritremata elevated, the most elevated state observed in 
<taxonomicName authority="De &amp; Bueno-Villegas &amp; Rafael, 2021" authorityName="De &amp; Bueno-Villegas &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="2021" class="Diplopoda" family="Aphelidesmidae" genus="Haematotropis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="driki" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Haematotropis driki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[304,393,475,501]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[304,393,475,501]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
Besides that, the gonopod of this species has peculiar characteristics such as the distal region of the slightly curved dorsal acropodite (
<figureCitation box="[600,738,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 33" captionStartId="46.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[214,1373,181,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-22@46.[214,1373,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURE 33. Right gonopod of Haematotropis driki sp. nov., holotype ♂ (MNRJ). A. Mesal view. B. Dorsal view. C. Lateral view. D. Ventral view. Yellow scale indicates when VP1 exceeds the width of ventral region of acropodite. Abbreviations: Ac = acropodite; Ca = cannula; Cx = coxa; LP1 = Lateral Process 1; Pf = Prefemur; S = Solenomere; Sg = spermatic groove; Ste = setae; VP1 = Ventral Process 1. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5653803" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5653803/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Fig. 33A–D</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="De &amp; Bueno-Villegas &amp; Rafael, 2021" authorityName="De &amp; Bueno-Villegas &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="2021" box="[756,842,511,537]" class="Diplopoda" family="Aphelidesmidae" genus="Haematotropis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="driki" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[756,776,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[789,842,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">driki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[848,937,511,537]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[848,937,511,537]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
shows characters for the genus: anterolateral teeth in rings 2–4 (
<figureCitation box="[358,447,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1714,1738]" captionTargetBox="[281,1307,181,1690]" captionTargetId="figure-22@8.[281,1307,181,1690]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 2. General somatic features of Haematotropis Jeekel, 2000. A. H. jurutiensis sp. nov., non-type ♂ (MPEG), body ring 7, ventral view. B. H. jurutiensis sp. nov., non-type ♂ (MPEG), body ring 9 (highlighting the microgranulations), ventral view. C. H. jurutiensis sp. nov., non-type ♂ (MPEG), body ring 7, red arrow indicates the wrinkles close to paranota, ventral view. D. H. jurutiensis sp. nov., non-type ♂ (MPEG), body ring 8, red arrow indicates rounded projections on ventral surfaces, ventral view. E. H. jurutiensis sp. nov., non-type ♂ (MPEG), metazonite of body ring 8, red arrow indicates the microgranulations on anterior and posterior margins, dorsal view. F. H. megalcensis sp. nov. non-type ♂ (IBSP), body ring 10, red arrow indicates the microgranulations on anterior and posterior margins, ventral view. G. H. callipa, holotype ♂ (MfN), head and body rings 1–4, red arrow indicates a depression on collum or anterolateral teeth, dorsalateral view. Scale bars: 300 μm (A, E), 200 μm (C, D, F), 100 μm (B), 1 mm (G)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5653710" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5653710/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Fig. 2G</figureCitation>
), the gonopod with cup-shaped acropodite in the median region (
<figureCitation box="[1167,1269,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 33" captionStartId="46.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[214,1373,181,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-22@46.[214,1373,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURE 33. Right gonopod of Haematotropis driki sp. nov., holotype ♂ (MNRJ). A. Mesal view. B. Dorsal view. C. Lateral view. D. Ventral view. Yellow scale indicates when VP1 exceeds the width of ventral region of acropodite. Abbreviations: Ac = acropodite; Ca = cannula; Cx = coxa; LP1 = Lateral Process 1; Pf = Prefemur; S = Solenomere; Sg = spermatic groove; Ste = setae; VP1 = Ventral Process 1. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5653803" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5653803/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Fig. 33D</figureCitation>
), and the distal region curved ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[428,567,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 33" captionStartId="46.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[214,1373,181,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-22@46.[214,1373,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURE 33. Right gonopod of Haematotropis driki sp. nov., holotype ♂ (MNRJ). A. Mesal view. B. Dorsal view. C. Lateral view. D. Ventral view. Yellow scale indicates when VP1 exceeds the width of ventral region of acropodite. Abbreviations: Ac = acropodite; Ca = cannula; Cx = coxa; LP1 = Lateral Process 1; Pf = Prefemur; S = Solenomere; Sg = spermatic groove; Ste = setae; VP1 = Ventral Process 1. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5653803" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5653803/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Fig. 33A–D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,671,618,645]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1437,151,717]" box="[199,671,618,645]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,618,644]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[359,432,619,645]" name="Brazil" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Brazil</collectingCountry>
: Amazonas (
<figureCitation box="[575,658,618,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 51" captionStartId="66.[151,250,1873,1897]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1092,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-94@66.[151,1436,1092,1849]" captionTargetPageId="66" captionText="FIGURE 51. Distribution of Haematotropis Jeekel, 2000. Black symbol = H. paraensis sp. nov., blue symbol = H. poranga sp. nov., orange symbol = H. driki sp. nov., pink symbol = H. melgacensis sp. nov., red symbol = H. mosaica sp. nov., white symbol = H. tysoni sp. nov., yellow symbol = H. divergens comb. nov. (Chamberlin, 1918)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5653855" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5653855/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Fig. 51</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="45" pageNumber="46" type="etymology">
